\fs20 \cf2 Prepared 2026-07-17\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\fs21 \cf0 This questionnaire contains only decisions that remain unresolved after the first two rounds. The following are already treated as settled and are not being asked again: TECL-only; one user; always-on appliance; scheduled model-agnostic remote frontier agent; deterministic Gold verdict; autonomous candidate authoring; automatic Gold-to-leaderboard publication; no staging board or Trade Roster; normal active-strategy changes require Max; brokerage remains manual for 3.x; iOS is later; and only Max decides when 4.x begins.\
For each item, type after "Answer." If the suggested default matches your intent, "accept default" is enough. These questions are intentionally precise because a coding agent should not invent these rules.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf3 Questionnaire process rule:
\f1\b0 \cf0  After Max finishes each questionnaire round, the reviewing agent must read the complete answers and update README.md, charter.md, decisions.md, and every affected pillar plan before preparing another round or a coding handoff. The answered questionnaire is preserved unchanged as source evidence; the active Markdown documents become the current project truth. Contradictions must be reconciled explicitly, and superseded decisions must remain marked in the decision log. No round is complete merely because the answer file exists.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa220\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 A. Gold: the exact promise and economic gate\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs21 \cf0 1.	Gold wording.
\f1\b0  Is this the right final claim?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa100\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 "Gold is Montauk's highest current certification of an exact, frozen strategy configuration. Under a named validation-contract version and data vintage, it beat the defined TECL buy-and-hold benchmark on every required real-data horizon using the deployable execution model, passed every mandatory correctness, robustness, and search-wide anti-overfitting criterion, and remains current under Montauk's forward-monitoring rules. Gold means Montauk detected no disqualifying failure to the strongest extent supported by available evidence. It does not prove that overfitting is absent or guarantee any future call or return."\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 2.	Universal validation versus search history.
\f1\b0  Do you agree that every survivor should face the same mandatory gates, while the statistical correction still becomes stricter when the strategy was selected from a broader or more adaptive search?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: yes. Who authored a strategy does not change the visible gates, but millions of feedback-informed attempts cannot be treated like one untouched hypothesis.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer: yes no matter where the strategy comes from the backtesting and validations are the same
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 3.	Retire T0/T1/T2 routing.
\f1\b0  Should Montauk 3.0 retire validation routes that skip or reweight gates based on whether a candidate was human-preregistered, simple, or AI/discovery-authored?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: yes; one maximum-strength contract, with selection provenance incorporated inside the relevant tests rather than by omitting tests.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 4.	Required real-data horizons.
\f1\b0  Which named real-data periods must independently beat B&H for Gold? Please define the windows, for example: all real TECL history, a fixed recent five-year window, and one or more fixed rolling/stress windows.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: all available real history plus a fixed recent window; use named stress windows as required diagnostics only if they are frozen before search.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 5.	Rolling B&H demotion.
\f1\b0  What exact rolling underperformance should make a current Gold strategy lose Gold: window length, allowed margin below B&H, minimum observations/trades, and how many consecutive evaluations must fail?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: require a predeclared persistence rule rather than revoking on one noisy daily crossing.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 6.	Synthetic catastrophic veto.
\f1\b0  Synthetic history is diagnostic, but you also want an extreme synthetic failure to matter. What result is catastrophic enough to block Gold, if any?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: define one conservative veto such as ruin, unrecoverable drawdown, or severe B&H underperformance across a broad majority of predeclared synthetic regimes; do not count synthetic outperformance as independent proof.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 7.	Deployable fill timing.
\f1\b0  If a signal is calculated after a day's close, should Gold economics require execution at the next actually available price, with same-close results shown only as an optimistic diagnostic?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: yes. A strategy cannot know the closing signal and fill at that same close.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 8.	B&H comparator contract.
\f1\b0  Should B&H use the same initial date, deployable purchase timing, distributions, transaction costs, and treatment of unavailable/warm-up bars as the strategy? What return should risk-off cash earn?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: freeze every comparator detail and compare unrounded values under matched timing and costs.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 9.	Evidence of beating B&H.
\f1\b0  Is a point estimate barely above 1.0 enough, or must a one-sided lower confidence bound exceed B&H?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: lower confidence bound above B&H, accepting that the Gold board may sometimes be empty. This matches your preference to avoid false Gold.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 10.	Minimum evidence.
\f1\b0  Should Gold require a minimum number of trades, minimum track-record length, minimum independent regimes, or a combination? May a structurally simple strategy qualify with very few trades?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: use a combination with an explicit insufficient-evidence result rather than allowing a high point estimate to hide a tiny sample.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 11.	Mandatory planks versus composite score.
\f1\b0  Must every required validation dimension clear its own minimum, or may exceptional strength elsewhere offset a weak or failed dimension?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: mandatory minima for every load-bearing plank. Montauk Score ranks eligible Gold rows; it never rescues a failed Gold gate.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 12.	Score versus probability.
\f1\b0  Until enough real forward outcomes exist to calibrate a probability, should the UI say "Validation Score 78/100" rather than "78% confidence"?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: yes. A weighted composite is not automatically a 78% probability that the edge is real.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 13.	Missing and skipped validation.
\f1\b0  Should missing, budget-skipped, insufficient-variant, or unverifiable required evidence always prevent Gold unless a predeclared equivalent test is explicitly marked not applicable?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: yes; never silently drop a missing dimension and renormalize the remaining score upward.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 14.	Recent performance role.
\f1\b0  Should recent performance be a hard Gold requirement, a ranking weight, a demotion trigger, or all three with different rules?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: fixed recent horizon as one hard eligibility gate, recent strength as a ranking input, and a separate persistent rolling rule for live demotion.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 15.	Empty-board tolerance.
\f1\b0  Are you willing for a rigorous contract to produce zero Gold strategies temporarily, rather than lower the bar to guarantee an active Gold row?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: yes; then use the separately defined no-Gold human-decision state.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa220\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
