\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 B. Search breadth, continual learning, and honest counting\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs21 \cf0 16.	Search-campaign identity.
\f1\b0  How should one statistical search campaign be bounded: by family version, agent batch, data vintage, methodology version, elapsed time, or a combination?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: preserve all levels and let the correction use family, campaign, and lifetime/board context rather than pretending one boundary erases earlier selection.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 17.	What must be counted.
\f1\b0  Should Montauk record all agent-proposed families, invalid/rejected submissions, configurations actually cheap-screened, full backtests, validation attempts, and feedback-driven batches for selection-bias accounting?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: yes. A combination only declared but never evaluated is not a tested configuration, but the mechanism-level selection event should still be logged.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 18.	Agent learning from results.
\f1\b0  Do you accept that letting the agent read failures and the leaderboard is desirable but makes subsequent ideation adaptive to the same TECL history, so the validator must account for that selection?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: yes. This learning is a feature; pretending it is statistically free would be the problem.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 19.	Board-level multiple testing.
\f1\b0  Should a candidate be barred from Gold until Montauk also establishes that it survives a board/search-wide test such as SPA, White's Reality Check, Romano-Wolf, or a validated equivalent?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: yes; the exact method should be selected and audited by the validation workstream, not by the ideation agent.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 20.	Lifetime multiplicity.
\f1\b0  Does selection-bias history ever reset? If so, only after what kind of data or methodology change?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: do not erase history. Version it, and distinguish prior search under old data/contracts from current search while retaining lifetime context.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 21.	Family similarity.
\f1\b0  May related configurations remain separate leaderboard rows while being clustered as one dependent family for statistical correction and Chimera voting?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: yes. Presentation identity and statistical independence are different questions.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 22.	Protected exploration floor.
\f1\b0  What minimum share of discovery compute should remain reserved for unusual mechanisms even when promising lanes are producing survivors?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: start at 10%, allow adaptation within bounds, and report the realized allocation rather than pretending it is scientifically optimal.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs21 \cf0 23.	Retired-family sampling.
\f1\b0  Should a retired family receive a small monthly/new-data sample, and what event permits deeper reopening: meaningful traction, complementary primitive, champion weakness, or material redesign?\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 Suggested default: small periodic samples plus event-triggered reopening; never equate one failed search space with permanent proof that a mechanism cannot work.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa220\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Answer:
\f1\i0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa220\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 C. Strategy representation and untrusted execution\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs20 \cf0 Fixed representation decision: Rust is the production strategy/evaluation language and the agent does not choose another language. The normal agent output is one schema-constrained declarative family specification, not strategy source code and not a hand-written list of configurations. Rust validates the typed logic graph and constraints, compiles one internal execution plan, then generates and batch-evaluates exact configurations as data. The isolated Rust family-module escape hatch is staged and disabled until its containment, causality, determinism, resource, and parity acceptance tests pass. Python is reference/testing only.\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\sa80\partightenfactor0

\fs21 \cf0 24.	Rust representation path - DECIDED.
\f1\b0  Montauk begins declarative-first: the agent submits one typed family/search-space specification, while Rust generates valid exact configurations and batch-tests them. The isolated agent-authored Rust-module path is enabled only after its acceptance suite passes. This is intended to maximize test speed and prevent implementation/configuration errors without permanently blocking novel mechanisms.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\partightenfactor0

